        "title": "This code keep getting else without if errors",
        "body": "<p>This code keeps getting if without else errors. I couldn't see the problem here. Please help.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.util.Scanner;\n\npublic class TempOut {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        //variable\n        double t;\n        double v;\n        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);\n\n        //inputs\n        System.out.print(\"Give temperature(C): \");\n        t = input.nextDouble();\n        System.out.print(\"Give wind velocity(km/h): \");\n        v = input.nextDouble();\n\n        //formula\n        if (((t&gt;=-50) &amp; (t=&lt;5)) | 3&gt;=v) \n        {\n            double formula = 13.12 + (2*(0.6251*t)) - (11.37*v) + ((0.3965*t)*v);\n            System.out.print(\"The wind chill temperature is : \"+formula);\n        }\n        else {\n            if (((t&lt;-50) &amp; (t&gt;5)) | v=&lt;3) \n            {\n            System.out.print(\"Formula not suitable\");\n            }\n            else {\n                System.out.print(\"Invalid input\");\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>It says on every 'else' there's an error.<\/p>\n",
