    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8463bf535c4b8106a23108d1dcfbf79d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 6229267,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4846598,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4846598/hearner",
                "reputation": 2707,
                "display_name": "Hearner",
                "accept_rate": 67
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540698,
            "creation_date": 1533540393,
            "body": "<pre><code> if (((t&gt;=-50) &amp; (t=&lt;5)) | 3&gt;=v) \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>is all wrong:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>&amp;<\/code> and <code>|<\/code> are <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/op3.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">bitwise operators<\/a>. What you want is <code>&amp;&amp;<\/code> and <code>||<\/code> which are <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/opsummary.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Conditional Operators<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Logical operators allowed are : ==, != , > , >=  , &lt;  , &lt;= (See documentation <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/opsummary.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Here<\/a>). You <code>(t=&lt;5)<\/code> doesn't exist, what you want is <code>(t&lt;=5)<\/code><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>In the end, your <code>if<\/code> statement should be :<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if (((t &gt;= -50) &amp;&amp; (t &lt;= 5)) || 3 &gt;= v) \n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702519,
            "question_id": 51702439,
            "last_edit_date": 1533540698
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/9i3ex.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 7147888,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5462988,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5462988/anoopknr",
                "reputation": 3385,
                "display_name": "anoopknr"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540734,
            "creation_date": 1533540734,
            "body": "<p>Yo have many mistakes both <code>if-conditions<\/code> in your code .<\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>You used <code>&amp;<\/code> instead of <code>&amp;&amp;<\/code> and <code>|<\/code> instead of <code>||<\/code>  .<\/li>\n<li>You used <code>=&lt;<\/code> instead of <code>&lt;=<\/code> .<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>Modified code :-<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.util.Scanner;\n\npublic class Main {// TempOut {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        // variable\n        double t;\n        double v;\n        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);\n\n        // inputs\n        System.out.print(\"Give temperature(C): \");\n        t = input.nextDouble();\n        System.out.print(\"Give wind velocity(km/h): \");\n        v = input.nextDouble();\n\n        // formula\n        if ((t &gt;= -50 &amp;&amp; t &lt;= 5) || (3 &gt;= v)) // not if (((t&gt;=-50) &amp; (t=&lt;5)) | 3&gt;=v)\n        {\n            double formula = 13.12 + (2 * (0.6251 * t)) - (11.37 * v) + ((0.3965 * t) * v);\n            System.out.print(\"The wind chill temperature is : \" + formula);\n        } else {\n            if (((t &lt; -50) &amp;&amp; (t &gt; 5)) || v &lt;= 3) // not if (((t&lt;-50) &amp; (t&gt;5)) | v=&lt;3)\n            {\n                System.out.print(\"Formula not suitable\");\n            } else {\n                System.out.print(\"Invalid input\");\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Make sure that you do not make <strong>syntax<\/strong> errors.<\/p>\n\n<p>Output :-<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Give temperature(C): 2\nGive wind velocity(km/h): 5\nThe wind chill temperature is : -37.26459999999999\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702595,
            "question_id": 51702439
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a3f1fb7c9980b89d4742f6368065829f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 10398651,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7667684,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7667684/devendra-kumar",
                "reputation": 96,
                "display_name": "Devendra Kumar"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540938,
            "creation_date": 1533540938,
            "body": "<p><strong>Correct code:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if (((t&gt;=-50) &amp; (t&gt;=5)) | 3&gt;=v) \n        {\n            double formula = 13.12 + (2*(0.6251*t)) - (11.37*v) + ((0.3965*t)*v);\n            System.out.print(\"The wind chill temperature is : \"+formula);\n        }\n        else {\n            if (((t&lt;-50) &amp; (t&gt;5)) | v&gt;=3) \n            {\n            System.out.print(\"Formula not suitable\");\n            }\n            else {\n                System.out.print(\"Invalid input\");\n            }\n        }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You are using<br>\nif (((t>=-50) &amp; (t=&lt;5)) | <strong>3>=v<\/strong>) and if (((t&lt;-50) &amp; (t>5)) | <strong>v=&lt;3<\/strong>) .<\/p>\n\n<p>Look carefully this condition(Bold Cheractor) in correct code and your code.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702648,
            "question_id": 51702439
        }
